Here's a summary of the RoboMind project:

RoboMind Project Summary
Purpose
An educational AI project (SE444 course) where students build a rational AI agent that navigates a 2D grid world. The project teaches core AI concepts across 4 progressive phases:

Phase 1: Search algorithms (BFS, UCS, A*)
Phase 2: Propositional logic reasoning
Phase 3: Bayesian/probabilistic inference
Phase 4: Hybrid agent integrating all three
Students implement the AI algorithms from scratch — the environment, visualization, and testing harness are pre-provided.

How to Run

pip install -r requirements.txt

python main.py --demo              # Interactive pygame grid visualization
python main.py --test-search       # Test BFS, UCS, A*
python main.py --test-logic        # Test logic agent
python main.py --test-probability  # Test Bayesian agent
python main.py --test-hybrid       # Test integrated agent
python main.py --experiment all    # Run all experiments
Libraries Used
Library	Version	Purpose
pygame	2.5.2	Grid world visualization (interactive display)
numpy	1.24.3	Numerical computations
matplotlib	3.7.2	Performance plots and analysis
No AI/ML libraries — algorithms must be implemented from scratch.

APIs / Interfaces
No external APIs. The project uses an internal GridWorld environment API (environment.py) with methods like:

get_neighbors(pos) — 4-connected valid neighbors
is_valid(pos) / is_goal(pos) — cell queries
get_cost(pos1, pos2) — movement cost
manhattan_distance() / euclidean_distance() — heuristics
render() — pygame visualization
CLI is built with Python's argparse.

